Class: KeyVaultClient

KeyVaultClient

Initializes a new instance of the KeyVaultClient class.

Constructor

new KeyVaultClient(credentials, optionsopt)

Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Description
credentials credentials Credentials needed for the client to connect to Azure.
options object <optional>
 The parameter options
Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
filters Array <optional>
 Filters to be added to the request pipeline
requestOptions object <optional>
 Options for the underlying request object Options doc
noRetryPolicy boolean <optional>
 If set to true, turn off default retry policy
apiVersion string <optional>
 Client Api Version.
acceptLanguage string <optional>
 Gets or sets the preferred language for the response.
longRunningOperationRetryTimeout number <optional>
 Gets or sets the retry timeout in seconds for Long Running Operations. Default value is 30.
generateClientRequestId boolean <optional>
 When set to true a unique x-ms-client-request-id value is generated and included in each request. Default is true.

createCertificate(vaultBaseUrl, certificateName, optionsopt, optionalCallbackopt) → {function|Promise}

Creates a new certificate. If this is the first version, the certificate resource is created.
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Description
vaultBaseUrl string The vault name, for example https://myvault.vault.azure.net.
certificateName string The name of the certificate.
options object <optional>
 Optional Parameters.
Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
certificatePolicy object <optional>
 The management policy for the certificate.
Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
keyProperties object <optional>
 Properties of the key backing a certificate.
Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
exportable boolean <optional>
 Indicates if the private key can be exported.
keyType string <optional>
 The key type.
keySize number <optional>
 The key size in bytes. For example; 1024 or 2048.
reuseKey boolean <optional>
 Indicates if the same key pair will be used on certificate renewal.
secretProperties object <optional>
 Properties of the secret backing a certificate.
Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
contentType string <optional>
 The media type (MIME type).
x509CertificateProperties object <optional>
 Properties of the X509 component of a certificate.
Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
subject string <optional>
 The subject name. Should be a valid X509 distinguished Name.
ekus array <optional>
 The enhanced key usage.
subjectAlternativeNames object <optional>
 The subject alternative names.
Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
emails array <optional>
 Email addresses.
dnsNames array <optional>
 Domain names.
upns array <optional>
 User principal names.
keyUsage array <optional>
 List of key usages.
validityInMonths number <optional>
 The duration that the ceritifcate is valid in months.
lifetimeActions array <optional>
 Actions that will be performed by Key Vault over the lifetime of a certificate.
issuerParameters object <optional>
 Parameters for the issuer of the X509 component of a certificate.
Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
name string <optional>
 Name of the referenced issuer object or reserved names; for example, 'Self' or 'Unknown'.
certificateType string <optional>
 Type of certificate to be requested from the issuer provider.
attributes object <optional>
 The certificate attributes.
certificateAttributes object <optional>
 The attributes of the certificate (optional).
Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
enabled boolean <optional>
 Determines whether the object is enabled.
notBefore date <optional>
 Not before date in UTC.
expires date <optional>
 Expiry date in UTC.
tags object <optional>
 Application specific metadata in the form of key-value pairs.
customHeaders object <optional>
 Headers that will be added to the request
optionalCallback function <optional>
 The optional callback.

createKey(vaultBaseUrl, keyName, kty, optionsopt, optionalCallbackopt) → {function|Promise}

Creates a new key, stores it, then returns key parameters and attributes to the client. The create key operation can be used to create any key type in Azure Key Vault. If the named key already exists, Azure Key Vault creates a new version of the key. Authorization: Requires the keys/create permission.
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Description
vaultBaseUrl string The vault name, for example https://myvault.vault.azure.net.
keyName string The name for the new key. The system will generate the version name for the new key.
kty string The type of key to create. For valid key types, see JsonWebKeyType. Supported JsonWebKey key types (kty) for Elliptic Curve, RSA, HSM, Octet. Possible values include: 'EC', 'RSA', 'RSA-HSM', 'oct'
options object <optional>
 Optional Parameters.
Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
keySize number <optional>
 The key size in bytes. For example, 1024 or 2048.
keyOps array <optional>
keyAttributes object <optional>
Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
enabled boolean <optional>
 Determines whether the object is enabled.
notBefore date <optional>
 Not before date in UTC.
expires date <optional>
 Expiry date in UTC.
tags object <optional>
 Application specific metadata in the form of key-value pairs.
customHeaders object <optional>
 Headers that will be added to the request
optionalCallback function <optional>
 The optional callback.
Source:
  • keyVaultClient.js, line 8627
Returns:
If a callback was passed as the last parameter then it returns the callback else returns a Promise. {Promise} A promise is returned
Type
function | Promise

deleteKey(vaultBaseUrl, keyName, optionsopt, optionalCallbackopt) → {function|Promise}

Deletes a key of any type from storage in Azure Key Vault. The delete key operation cannot be used to remove individual versions of a key. This operation removes the cryptographic material associated with the key, which means the key is not usable for Sign/Verify, Wrap/Unwrap or Encrypt/Decrypt operations. Authorization: Requires the keys/delete permission.

importKey(vaultBaseUrl, keyName, key, optionsopt, optionalCallbackopt) → {function|Promise}

Imports an externally created key, stores it, and returns key parameters and attributes to the client. The import key operation may be used to import any key type into an Azure Key Vault. If the named key already exists, Azure Key Vault creates a new version of the key. Authorization: requires the keys/import permission.
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Description
vaultBaseUrl string The vault name, for example https://myvault.vault.azure.net.
keyName string Name for the imported key.
key object The Json web key
Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
kid string <optional>
 Key identifier.
kty string <optional>
 Supported JsonWebKey key types (kty) for Elliptic Curve, RSA, HSM, Octet. Kty is usually set to RSA. Possible values include: 'EC', 'RSA', 'RSA-HSM', 'oct'
keyOps array <optional>
n buffer <optional>
 RSA modulus.
e buffer <optional>
 RSA public exponent.
d buffer <optional>
 RSA private exponent.
dp buffer <optional>
 RSA private key parameter.
dq buffer <optional>
 RSA private key parameter.
qi buffer <optional>
 RSA private key parameter.
p buffer <optional>
 RSA secret prime.
q buffer <optional>
 RSA secret prime, with p < q.
k buffer <optional>
 Symmetric key.
t buffer <optional>
 HSM Token, used with 'Bring Your Own Key'.
options object <optional>
 Optional Parameters.
Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
hsm boolean <optional>
 Whether to import as a hardware key (HSM) or software key.
keyAttributes object <optional>
 The key management attributes.
Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
enabled boolean <optional>
 Determines whether the object is enabled.
notBefore date <optional>
 Not before date in UTC.
expires date <optional>
 Expiry date in UTC.
tags object <optional>
 Application specific metadata in the form of key-value pairs.
customHeaders object <optional>
 Headers that will be added to the request
optionalCallback function <optional>
 The optional callback.
Source:
  • keyVaultClient.js, line 8813

importKeyWithHttpOperationResponse(vaultBaseUrl, keyName, key, optionsopt) → {Promise}

Imports an externally created key, stores it, and returns key parameters and attributes to the client. The import key operation may be used to import any key type into an Azure Key Vault. If the named key already exists, Azure Key Vault creates a new version of the key. Authorization: requires the keys/import permission.

The update key operation changes specified attributes of a stored key and can be applied to any key type and key version stored in Azure Key Vault. importKey(vaultBaseUrl, keyName, key, optionsopt, optionalCallbackopt) → {function|Promise}

Imports an externally created key, stores it, and returns key parameters and attributes to the client. The import key operation may be used to import any key type into an Azure Key Vault. If the named key already exists, Azure Key Vault creates a new version of the key. Authorization: requires the keys/import permission.
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Description
vaultBaseUrl string The vault name, for example https://myvault.vault.azure.net.
keyName string Name for the imported key.
key object The Json web key
Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
kid string <optional>
 Key identifier.
kty string <optional>
 Supported JsonWebKey key types (kty) for Elliptic Curve, RSA, HSM, Octet. Kty is usually set to RSA. Possible values include: 'EC', 'RSA', 'RSA-HSM', 'oct'
keyOps array <optional>
n buffer <optional>
 RSA modulus.
e buffer <optional>
 RSA public exponent.
d buffer <optional>
 RSA private exponent.
dp buffer <optional>
 RSA private key parameter.
dq buffer <optional>
 RSA private key parameter.
qi buffer <optional>
 RSA private key parameter.
p buffer <optional>
 RSA secret prime.
q buffer <optional>
 RSA secret prime, with p < q.
k buffer <optional>
 Symmetric key.
t buffer <optional>
 HSM Token, used with 'Bring Your Own Key'.
options object <optional>
 Optional Parameters.
Properties
Name Type Attributes Description
hsm boolean <optional>
 Whether to import as a hardware key (HSM) or software key.
keyAttributes object <optional>
 The key management attributes.
Properties
Name Type Attributes Description

 Determines whether the object is enabled.
notBefore date <optional>
 Not before date in UTC.
expires date <optional>
 Expiry date in UTC.

 Application specific metadata in the form of key-value pairs.

 The optional callback.

updateKey(keyIdentifier, optionsopt, optionalCallbackopt) → {function|Promise}

The update key operation changes specified attributes of a stored key and can be applied to any key type and key version stored in Azure Key Vault. The cryptographic material of a key itself cannot be changed. In order to perform this operation, the key must already exist in the Key Vault. Authorization: requires the keys/update permission.
Parameters:
Name Type Attributes Description
keyIdentifier string The key identifier. It may or may not contain a version path. If a version is not provided, the latest key version is used.
